The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, September 27, 2002 				 Faber to expand 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, Sept. 26: Faber Heatkraft Industries Ltd, a joint venture between the $ 200-million Faber SpA of Italy amp; Heatkraft of Pune today announced major expansion and diversification plans for the domestic kitchen appliances market. Faber India, a leading payer in the Indian electric kitchen chimney, cooking range and gas hob market, is now entering other related segments, to provide one-stop kitchen solutions. 																								The company has announced a fresh investment of Rs 12 crore to fund its expansion and diversification programmes and is targeting a turnover of Rs 100 crore by the end of the next fiscal. Turnover this fiscal, is estimated to be around Rs 40 crore. 
